# Navigation and UI Fixes Walkthrough

## Overview
This update focused on resolving compilation errors and improving the navigation flow based on user feedback. Specifically, we fixed issues preventing the "Go to Download Page" button from working and removed the unnecessary hamburger menu.

## Changes

### 1. Fixed Compilation Errors
- **`CS0272` (Property Access)**: The `NavigationView.SelectedItem` setter was inaccessible. We resolved this by exposing a public [NavigateTo(string tag)](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/MainWindow.xaml.cs#165-192) method in [MainWindow.xaml.cs](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/MainWindow.xaml.cs) and using that for navigation instead of setting the property directly.
- **`MC3072` (XAML Property)**: Fixed `IsPaneToggleButtonVisible` error in [MainWindow.xaml](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/MainWindow.xaml) by renaming it to the correct `IsPaneToggleVisible` property.
- **`CS1513` (Missing Brace)**: Fixed a syntax error in [VersionSettingsPage.xaml.cs](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Views/VersionSettingsPage.xaml.cs) where a closing brace was missing.

### 2. UI/UX Improvements
- **Hamburger Menu Removal**: Hidden the hamburger menu (three lines) in the sidebar as requested (`IsPaneToggleVisible="False"`).
- **Functional Buttons**:
  - **"Go to Download Page"**: Now correctly navigates to the Download tab using the new [NavigateTo](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/MainWindow.xaml.cs#165-192) method.
  - **"Version Selection"**: Navigates to the Version Selector page, and upon selection, correctly redirects to the settings for the chosen version.

## Verification
- **Build**: The application should now build without `CS0272`, `MC3072`, or `CS1513` errors.
- **Navigation**:
  - Click "Mod Management" -> "Go to Download Page": Should switch to Download tab.
  - Sidebar: Hamburger menu should be gone.
  - Sidebar navigation (Home, Resources, etc.) should still work correctly.

## Next Steps
- Verify the "Version Selection" flow handles the back stack correctly.
- Continue implementing the Export functionality.
